Pre-Game Insights: Austria will be looking to end an all-time streak when facing Netherlands at Euro 2024 on Tuesday evening.
Rangnick took the opportunity to turn down the opportunity to join Bayern Munich to invest in the national team project.
Austria has collected three points from their opening two games and at least third position is assured, but they will have to halt an historic run if they want to earn any further points.
Netherlands are looking to defeat Austria for the third successive time at a major tournament.
Netherlands are bidding to extend their unbeaten record in group-stage fixtures at major tournaments to 12 matches (nine wins, two draws).
Miscellaneous Highlights: Austria have lost each of their last seven encounters with Netherlands, representing the longest such run against a single opponent in their entire history, dating back to a friendly fixture in Vienna in May 1990.
Netherlands have scored at least twice in the following seven matches, netting a total of 20 times in friendlies, qualifiers and at Euro 2020.
Austria have prevailed just twice versus Netherlands in the 13 contests that have taken place since 1974.
